title: Euro LIBOR Three Month Rate
description: Euro LIBOR Three Month Rate was at -0.58 percent on Wednesday November 9. Interbank Rate in the Euro Area averaged 1.46 percent from 1998 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 5.39 percent in October of 2008 and a record low of -0.62 percent in December of 2021. The three month euro LIBOR interest rate is the average interest rate at which a LIBOR contributor bank can obtain unsecured funding in the London interbank market for a three month period in euros. This page provides - Euro Area Three Month nterbank Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
